00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:27.870
PROFESSOR: We'll be talking
about the diode and charge

00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:29.830
separation inside
of a solar cell.

00:00:29.830 --> 00:00:31.540
So at the end of
last class, we ended

00:00:31.540 --> 00:00:33.680
with this little
demonstration right here,

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:36.690
where after much
discussion about band

00:00:36.690 --> 00:00:38.990
gaps and light
absorption, we agreed

00:00:38.990 --> 00:00:40.610
that that little
piece of silicon

00:00:40.610 --> 00:00:42.080
there should be
absorbing the light

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:46.420
and free charges should be
generated inside the silicon.

00:00:46.420 --> 00:00:48.800
But without some
fixed fields, some

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:51.810
built in field inside
of the silicon material,

00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:54.110
it wasn't possible to
measure any current output

00:00:54.110 --> 00:00:55.380
once we shown light on it.

00:00:55.380 --> 00:00:56.620
And that made sense.

00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:58.490
There were free charges
being generated,

00:00:58.490 --> 00:01:02.090
but due to Brownian motion,
there was no net charge flow.

00:01:02.090 --> 00:01:04.267
They were just moving
around with no net movement.

00:01:04.267 --> 00:01:05.850
And as a result,
there was no current.

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:08.580
Now if we attach the
batteries in series,

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:11.160
the batteries apply to field
across this little piece

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:15.110
of silicon resulting
in current flow-- more

00:01:15.110 --> 00:01:18.630
precisely, drift current
across that piece of silicon.

00:01:18.630 --> 00:01:20.580
And today we're
going to be talking

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:26.060
about how the solar cell device
has a built in electric field.

00:01:26.060 --> 00:01:28.407
So obviously we don't want
an external power source.

00:01:28.407 --> 00:01:30.490
We don't want to have a
set of batteries attached.

00:01:30.490 --> 00:01:34.130
That defeats the purpose of an
autonomous energy generation

00:01:34.130 --> 00:01:34.986
device.

00:01:34.986 --> 00:01:36.860
We'll be talking about
how the built in field

00:01:36.860 --> 00:01:38.670
inside of a solar
cell comes into being.

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:43.910
As we've followed in
