00:34:41.280 --> 00:34:45.219
because they're both affected
in a similar manner to that.

00:34:45.219 --> 00:34:48.030
So why don't you go ahead
and give it your best?

00:34:48.030 --> 00:34:53.270
Draw the energy band diagram
in terms of the electron energy

00:34:53.270 --> 00:34:54.590
and position.

00:34:54.590 --> 00:34:56.840
Notice your p-type on one
side, n-type on the other.

00:34:56.840 --> 00:34:59.120
You can assume that
the point of division

00:34:59.120 --> 00:35:01.599
is like right here
in the middle.

00:35:01.599 --> 00:35:03.140
And for those who
are a little quick,

00:35:03.140 --> 00:35:05.080
you can go on and draw
the relative magnitudes

00:35:05.080 --> 00:35:06.802
of electron drift and
diffusion currents.

00:35:06.802 --> 00:35:08.760
So why don't we give that
a quick, little shot?

00:35:08.760 --> 00:35:12.840
Maybe 30 seconds to think
about it and another 30 seconds

00:35:12.840 --> 00:35:15.110
to draw and chat over
