00:36:08.490 --> 00:36:11.820
have the band bending
down like this.

00:36:11.820 --> 00:36:14.510
So we would have the bands
higher on one side, lower

00:36:14.510 --> 00:36:15.740
on the other.

00:36:15.740 --> 00:36:18.570
The electron energy is
higher on the p-type side

00:36:18.570 --> 00:36:19.580
than the n-type side.

00:36:19.580 --> 00:36:21.246
So if we add one
electron to our system,

00:36:21.246 --> 00:36:23.350
for example a
photo-generated carrier

00:36:23.350 --> 00:36:26.317
from one photon coming
into our device,

00:36:26.317 --> 00:36:28.150
that electron will have
the natural tendency

00:36:28.150 --> 00:36:29.460
to go onto this side.

00:36:29.460 --> 00:36:32.000
It will be swept down.

00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:34.470
Note that the net
current flow inside

00:36:34.470 --> 00:36:37.050
of the device, in the absence
of an external excitation,

00:36:37.050 --> 00:36:41.410
like light or a battery pack
over here, an external bias

00:36:41.410 --> 00:36:44.340
voltage source, the net
current flow is zero.

00:36:44.340 --> 00:36:45.940
Because electron
diffusion is pointed

00:36:45.940 --> 00:36:47.840
in that direction
and electron drift

00:36:47.840 --> 00:36:49.175
pointed in that direction.

00:36:51.960 --> 00:36:53.330
All right, good.

00:36:53.330 --> 00:37:00.240
So now that we've done one
example, I wanted to-- oh,

00:37:00.240 --> 00:37:01.150
one last thing.

00:37:01.150 --> 00:37:02.167
So hole diffusion.

00:37:02.167 --> 00:37:03.750
So this is electron
diffusion pointing

00:37:03.750 --> 00:37:06.050
to the left and electron
drift pointing to the right.

00:37:06.050 --> 00:37:08.210
Hole diffusion is pointing
to the right and hole

00:37:08.210 --> 00:37:12.500
drift pointing to the
