00:37:41.070 --> 00:37:42.653
The forward bias
would look like that.

00:37:42.653 --> 00:37:44.590
The reverse bias
would look like that.

00:37:44.590 --> 00:37:45.180
OK.

00:37:45.180 --> 00:37:47.720
And now the big question is,
what do the band diagrams

00:37:47.720 --> 00:37:48.220
look like?

00:37:48.220 --> 00:37:49.710
How would these look?

00:37:53.480 --> 00:37:59.270
If we forward bias, if we
forward bias our device

00:37:59.270 --> 00:38:01.929
and we inject electrons
into this side right here,

00:38:01.929 --> 00:38:03.220
what would happen to our bands?

00:38:03.220 --> 00:38:04.678
What would you
expect would happen?

00:38:07.470 --> 00:38:11.560
We'll prove this out
in the next few slides,

00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:14.029
but I want to see how
people's intuition is

00:38:14.029 --> 00:38:14.820
doing this morning.

00:38:23.480 --> 00:38:26.410
So as you bias a device,
you're shifting one level

00:38:26.410 --> 00:38:27.332
relative to the other.

00:38:27.332 --> 00:38:29.540
And so the basic question
that you have to answer is,

00:38:29.540 --> 00:38:33.370
should it shift up or
should it shift down under

00:38:33.370 --> 00:38:36.410
Forward and reverse
