00:38:55.520 --> 00:38:56.702
Rationale?

00:38:56.702 --> 00:38:58.160
An easy way to
think about this is,

00:38:58.160 --> 00:39:00.618
if our battery is aligned with
our pn-junction in that way,

00:39:00.618 --> 00:39:02.740
and we're injecting
electrons into one side,

00:39:02.740 --> 00:39:05.140
we then have a large
electron diffusion current.

00:39:05.140 --> 00:39:07.450
We have the bands shifting
in this direction.

00:39:07.450 --> 00:39:10.600
Now the barrier, the energy
barrier for the electrons

00:39:10.600 --> 00:39:13.810
to overcome, to go from the
region of high concentration

00:39:13.810 --> 00:39:16.680
to the region of low
concentration, is smaller.

00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:18.930
And you'll get a larger
diffusion current as a result.

00:39:18.930 --> 00:39:21.480
More electrons will be moving
over that n-type silicon

00:39:21.480 --> 00:39:23.110
into the p-type silicon.

00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:26.090
And the drift current
will be smaller.

00:39:26.090 --> 00:39:29.600
Notice here, the balance of the
two, if you add them together,

00:39:29.600 --> 00:39:32.020
you have a net electron flow
in that direction, which

00:39:32.020 --> 00:39:33.910
means you have a
net current flow

00:39:33.910 --> 00:39:35.870
as defined by the flow
of positive charges

00:39:35.870 --> 00:39:37.346
in the other direction.

00:39:37.346 --> 00:39:39.380
A lot of definitions
to keep straight.

00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:42.770
Whereas, under reverse bias
here, you're shifting the bands

00:39:42.770 --> 00:39:44.490
like so.

00:39:44.490 --> 00:39:46.240
Because you have the
large electric field,

00:39:46.240 --> 00:39:49.720
the drift current will be
increased, but only slightly.

00:39:49.720 --> 00:39:54.080
Because there's a limited
number of carriers here

00:39:54.080 --> 00:39:57.070
that you can pull from
the p-type material.

00:39:57.070 --> 00:39:59.750
And the diffusion current is
going to be drastically reduced

00:39:59.750 --> 00:40:04.070
because now the energy barrier
is so large that the electrons

00:40:04.070 --> 00:40:06.470
have a very hard time getting
from the n-type material

00:40:06.470 --> 00:40:08.010
into the p-type material.

00:40:08.010 --> 00:40:10.910
And then that net current flow
is in the opposite direction.

00:40:13.374 --> 00:40:15.040
Does this make intuitive
sense to folks?

00:40:15.040 --> 00:40:15.540
Ashley.

00:40:15.540 --> 00:40:21.655
AUDIENCE: So when you touch
