00:42:27.770 --> 00:42:32.940
But what is driving the current
is mostly the drift current.

00:42:32.940 --> 00:42:34.790
It's pulling carriers
from-- essentially,

00:42:34.790 --> 00:42:35.998
through your external circle.

00:42:35.998 --> 00:42:38.770
Because carriers are moving
from the p-type to the n-type

00:42:38.770 --> 00:42:40.360
and creating that
charge imbalance

00:42:40.360 --> 00:42:43.860
resulting in the drift current.

00:42:43.860 --> 00:42:46.730
Why don't we continue
moving on just a little bit

00:42:46.730 --> 00:42:49.960
because we have some nice
