So V is at 0.

00:43:30.450 --> 00:43:32.710
And we know that we have
no net current flow.

00:43:32.710 --> 00:43:34.760
And so our current is
going to be at 0 as well.

00:43:34.760 --> 00:43:35.850
And so we know that
we're going to have

00:43:35.850 --> 00:43:37.360
one point on our
I-V curve that's

00:43:37.360 --> 00:43:39.890
going to be situated at 0, 0.

00:43:39.890 --> 00:43:41.990
Likewise, in this
case over here,

00:43:41.990 --> 00:43:44.872
we have electron diffusion
driving the circuit.

00:43:44.872 --> 00:43:46.830
And in the other, we have
electron drift, which

00:43:46.830 --> 00:43:48.440
is in the opposite direction.

00:43:48.440 --> 00:43:51.140
And so you'd expect
that the current flow

00:43:51.140 --> 00:43:53.840
in I under forward bias
conditions-- forward bias is

00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:55.990
positive-- would be
somewhere up here.

00:43:55.990 --> 00:43:57.970
And likewise,
under reverse bias,

00:43:57.970 --> 00:44:00.970
that our current would
be opposite the sign.

00:44:00.970 --> 00:44:03.110
So whereas we had positive
