for the electrons to pass over.

01:09:55.323 --> 01:10:00.080
So our diffusion current
practically vanishes.

01:10:00.080 --> 01:10:02.570
And our drift current
stays, more or less,

01:10:02.570 --> 01:10:05.300
constant all the way
throughout because there's only

01:10:05.300 --> 01:10:08.100
a finite carrier density,
a finite minority carrier

01:10:08.100 --> 01:10:10.510
concentration inside
of the p-type silicon.

01:10:10.510 --> 01:10:12.534
The thermally excited
carriers for instance,

01:10:12.534 --> 01:10:14.700
that are finding their way
to the junction and being

01:10:14.700 --> 01:10:15.830
drifted across.

01:10:15.830 --> 01:10:18.370
And that concentration
is virtually finite.

01:10:18.370 --> 01:10:21.560
At some point, you'll
reverse bias this so much

01:10:21.560 --> 01:10:24.850
that the carriers will
begin tunneling across

01:10:24.850 --> 01:10:27.740
from the valence band into
the conduction band over here

01:10:27.740 --> 01:10:30.640
and you'll have a catastrophic
failure of your device,

01:10:30.640 --> 01:10:33.237
but that's more of
an advanced point.

01:10:33.237 --> 01:10:33.737
Yeah.

01:10:33.737 --> 01:10:37.550
AUDIENCE: So does the x indicate
the coordinate of I and V

01:10:37.550 --> 01:10:38.360
at steady state?

01:10:38.360 --> 01:10:41.390
PROFESSOR: So the
entire line represents

01:10:41.390 --> 01:10:44.860
the I-V characteristic
under all biased conditions.

01:10:44.860 --> 01:10:49.150
The x represents the
current and voltage

01:10:49.150 --> 01:10:52.920
for this particular operating
point on the solar cell.

01:10:52.920 --> 01:10:54.190
On the I-V characteristic.

01:10:54.190 --> 01:10:55.980
So if you're under
forward bias condition.

01:10:55.980 --> 01:10:58.110
In other words,
your v is positive,

01:10:58.110 --> 01:11:01.340
you will have a positive current
flow through your device.

01:11:01.340 --> 01:11:04.490
Positive current flow,
electrons flowing that way.

01:11:04.490 --> 01:11:07.580
And under reverse bias,
notice the sign of the current

01:11:07.580 --> 01:11:09.925
is flipped because
now the electrons used

01:11:09.925 --> 01:11:10.800
to be going that way.

01:11:10.800 --> 01:11:13.100
The electrons are predominately
moving the other direction.

01:11:13.100 --> 01:11:15.280
The net current flow is
in the opposite direction.

01:11:15.280 --> 01:11:18.570
And the voltage is
also changing sign.

01:11:18.570 --> 01:11:20.212
AUDIENCE: You can
say, OK, I'm going

01:11:20.212 --> 01:11:21.779
to put myself in this voltage?

01:11:21.779 --> 01:11:22.570
PROFESSOR: Exactly.

01:11:22.570 --> 01:11:24.150
And that's important
because we want

01:11:24.150 --> 01:11:27.876
to be able to describe
what our current voltage

01:11:27.876 --> 01:11:29.250
characteristic is
of a solar cell

01:11:29.250 --> 01:11:32.000
because the product of
the two is the power.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:34.200
For efficiency, we want
to know what the power out

01:11:34.200 --> 01:11:35.429
of our solar cell is.

01:11:35.429 --> 01:11:37.220
And it's the product
of current and voltage

01:11:37.220 --> 01:11:41.560
that will give us the power
of our solar cell device.

